# Components

Three layers, each with a clear role:

| Layer | Folder | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| **Primitives** | `components/ui/` | Generic, reusable: `Button`, `Input`, `Textarea`, `Badge`, `StatusBadge`, `Modal`, `Spinner`, `PageLoader`, `ProductCardSkeleton`, `Toast` (+ `toast` helper, `ToastHost`) |
| **Common** | `components/common/` | Brand atoms: `Logo`, `GoldDivider`, `AnimatedReveal`, `SearchOverlay` |
| **Domain** | `cart/`, `product/`, `auth/`, `layout/` | Feature-bound, often consumes stores/hooks |

## Component Structure (the standard shape)

```jsx
import { cn } from '../../lib/utils'

export default function Thing({ variant = 'default', className, children, ...rest }) {
  return (
    <div className={cn('base classes', variantClasses[variant], className)} {...rest}>
      {children}
    </div>
  )
}
```

Rules:
- **Default export** for the main component. Named exports for variants (e.g. `Textarea`, `StatusBadge`, `PageLoader`).
- **`forwardRef`** for any focusable primitive (`Button`, `Input`, `Textarea` already do this).
- **Variants object** at module top, indexed by a `variant` prop.
- Last className parameter to `cn(...)` is always the consumer's `className`, so callers can override.

## Primitives — How to Use

### Button (`ui/Button.jsx`)
- `variant`: `outline` (default, `.btn-luxe`), `filled` (gold-fill), `dark` (black on light bg), `ghost`, `link`.
- `size`: `sm`, `md` (default), `lg`, `xl`.
- Pass `loading` for a spinner + auto-disable. Polymorphic via `as` prop.

### Input / Textarea (`ui/Input.jsx`)
- Props: `label`, `hint`, `error`, `dark` (true on dark surfaces — switches border colors).
- Style: underline-only on light, gold-underline on dark. Never a boxed input.
- Always pass `label` for accessibility — the wrapping `<label>` makes the input clickable.

### Badge / StatusBadge (`ui/Badge.jsx`)
- `variant`: `gold`, `plum`, `mauve`, `rose`, `ivory`, `outline`, `outline-dark`, `dark`, `muted`.
- `<StatusBadge status="shipped" />` maps order statuses to the right tone — use it everywhere status is shown.

### Modal (`ui/Modal.jsx`)
- Wraps Radix Dialog. **Centering uses Framer Motion's `x: '-50%', y: '-50%'`** — DO NOT swap to Tailwind `-translate-*` classes (they get overwritten by Framer's animated transform).
- `size`: `sm` `md` `lg` `xl`. Always use the title prop for screen readers.

### Toast (`ui/Toast.jsx`)
- Imperatively call `toast.success(title, description?)`, `toast.error(...)`, `toast.info(...)`.
- Provider lives in `main.jsx`; `<ToastHost />` is rendered in `App.jsx`. Don't add another provider.

### Spinner / PageLoader / ProductCardSkeleton (`ui/Spinner.jsx`)
- `<Spinner size="md" label="Loading" />` for inline loaders.
- `<PageLoader />` is the brand-pulsing NOVAËL wordmark — use for full-page initial loads.
- `<ProductCardSkeleton />` for product grids.

## Animation Patterns

We use **Framer Motion exclusively**. Tailwind animations are reserved for `shimmer`, `marquee`, `pulseGold`, `bounceSubtle` (defined in config).

### Standard scroll-reveal — use `AnimatedReveal`
```jsx
<AnimatedReveal y={40} duration={0.7}>
  <h2>Section heading</h2>
</AnimatedReveal>

<AnimatedReveal stagger={0.1}>
  <Item /><Item /><Item />
</AnimatedReveal>
```
The component uses the **luxe easing** `[0.16, 1, 0.3, 1]` — copy that easing for any custom motion to keep the brand feel consistent.

### Page transitions
Handled by `AppRouter`'s `<PageFade>` wrapper — don't add per-page enter animations to whole pages.

### Hover micro-interactions
Use `motion.div` with `whileHover` or CSS group-hover on Tailwind. `ProductCard.jsx` is the reference for image cross-fade on hover.

## Accessibility

- All icon-only buttons get `aria-label` (see `Navbar.jsx` Menu/Search/Cart).
- Form inputs get a visible `<label>` — already enforced by `Input` primitive.
- Modals/Toasts/Dropdowns use Radix → keyboard + screen-reader handled.
- Decorative SVGs (Logo, GoldDivider) have `aria-label="Novaël"` or `aria-hidden`.
- Color contrast: ivory on black is fine; never put `taupe` text on `ivory` for body copy (only for line-through / muted).

## Class Naming with Tailwind

- Order: layout → spacing → sizing → typography → colors → effects → motion.
- Brand letter-spacing: `tracking-[0.15em]` for headlines, `tracking-[0.2em]`–`tracking-[0.3em]` for uppercase labels.
- Brand text sizes for labels: `text-[10px]` or `text-[11px]` (uppercase, `font-medium`/`font-semibold`).
- Backdrop blur on overlays: `backdrop-blur-sm`/`-[6px]`. Z-index scale: nav `z-[800]`, drawer `z-[850]`, modal overlay `z-[900]`, modal content `z-[950]`, toast `z-[1000]`.
